0000192 ! smooth muscle cell\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:14002:intersection_of: UBERON:0000487 ! simple squamous epithelium\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:14005:relationship: composed_primarily_of CL:0000077 {source=\"FMA\"} ! mesothelial cell\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:14957:intersection_of: composed_primarily_of UBERON:0002394 ! bile duct\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:16954:relationship: composed_primarily_of CL:0000542 ! lymphocyte\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:17288:relationship: composed_primarily_of CL:0002064 ! pancreatic acinar cell\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:17539:intersection_of: composed_primarily_of UBERON:0002481 ! bone tissue\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:17577:intersection_of: composed_primarily_of UBERON:0002481 ! bone tissue\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:17611:intersection_of: composed_primarily_of UBERON:0002481 ! bone tissue\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:18012:def: \"The portion of the renal tubule that constitutes the proximal part of the loop of Henle, has low permeability to ions and urea, and is highly permeable to water; it consists of an initial short thick segment lined by low simple cuboidal epithelium and a long thin segment lined by simple squamous epithelium; however, this distinction is not as important physiologically as in the ascending limb, so often the two are treated as one structure.\" [MGI:anna, MP:0011341]\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:18234:relationship: composed_primarily_of UBERON:0001135 ! smooth muscle tissue\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:19136:def: \"The longest part of the male urethra contained in the corpus spongiosum and extending from the end of the membranous portion to the external urethral orifice; commencing below the inferior fascia of the urogenital diaphragm it passes forward and upward to the front of the symphysis pubis; and then, in the flaccid condition of the penis, it bends downward and forward; while narrow and of uniform size in the body of the penis, it is dilated behind, within the bulb, and again anteriorly within the glans penis, where it forms the fossa navicularis urethrae; the spongy urethra is lined by pseudostratified columnar epithelium proximally, and by stratified squamous epithelium distally.\" [MGI:anna, MP:0011779]\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:19347:property_value: external_ontology_notes \"FMA: nonkeratinizing stratified squamous epithelium; BTO: Vaginal epithelium is stratified squamous epithelium having a thickness of 15-200 microns; MA has single subclass (squamous)\" xsd:string {external_ontology=\"FMA\"}\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:19405:intersection_of: composed_primarily_of CL:0000448 ! white adipocyte\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:19436:intersection_of: composed_primarily_of CL:0000449 ! brown adipocyte\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:21152:intersection_of: composed_primarily_of UBERON:0002481 ! bone tissue\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:21179:intersection_of: composed_primarily_of UBERON:0002481 ! bone tissue\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:21329:intersection_of: composed_primarily_of UBERON:0002481 ! bone tissue\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:21361:intersection_of: composed_primarily_of UBERON:0002481 ! bone tissue\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:21394:intersection_of: composed_primarily_of UBERON:0002481 ! bone tissue\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:21434:intersection_of: composed_primarily_of UBERON:0002481 ! bone tissue\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:21834:intersection_of: composed_primarily_of UBERON:0002481 ! bone tissue\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:21970:intersection_of: composed_primarily_of UBERON:0002481 ! bone tissue\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:22048:intersection_of: composed_primarily_of UBERON:0002481 ! bone tissue\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:22093:intersection_of: composed_primarily_of UBERON:0002481 ! bone tissue\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:22137:intersection_of: composed_primarily_of UBERON:0002481 ! bone tissue\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:22702:intersection_of: composed_primarily_of UBERON:0002481 ! bone tissue\n