c/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:117351:intersection_of: has_part CL:0000076 ! squamous epithelial cell\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:117356:name: stratified squamous epithelium\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:117357:def: \"Multilaminar epithelium which consists of more than one layer of squamous cells only one layer of which is in contact with a basement membrane. Examples: keratinized stratified squamous epithelium, epithelium of wall of esophagus.[FMA].\" [FMA:45563, Wikipedia:Stratified_squamous_epithelium]\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:117365:intersection_of: has_part CL:0000076 ! squamous epithelial cell\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:117370:def: \"A non-keratinized stratified squamous epithelium that is part of a tongue.\" [OBOL:automatic]\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:117372:intersection_of: UBERON:0010304 ! non-keratinized stratified squamous epithelium\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:117434:is_a: UBERON:0010304 ! non-keratinized stratified squamous epithelium\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:117447:is_a: UBERON:0006915 ! stratified squamous epithelium\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:117487:intersection_of: composed_primarily_of CL:0000150 ! glandular epithelial cell\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:117494:intersection_of: composed_primarily_of CL:0000150 ! glandular epithelial cell\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:117683:relationship: composed_primarily_of CL:0000059 ! ameloblast\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:117913:relationship: composed_primarily_of GO:0045095 ! keratin filament\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:119892:intersection_of: composed_primarily_of UBERON:0000125 ! neural nucleus\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:120129:relationship: composed_primarily_of UBERON:0002036 {source=\"Wikipedia\"} ! striated muscle tissue\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:120998:property_value: development_notes \"You will still see the statement in some texts that the parts of the forestomach are derived from the embryonic esophagus, and that's the reason why (like the esophagus) they're lined with stratified squamous epithelium. This is open to doubt. While there is no doubt that the rumen, reticulum, and omasum are all derived from the embryonic foregut, there is evidence to indicate that all three come from that an area of the foregut homologous to the part that develops into the single stomach of non-ruminants. If this is so, then the forestomach can be considered diverticula (or derivatives) of the stomach proper, not the esophagus, despite the nature of the lining -- http://www.vetmed.vt.edu/education/curriculum/vm8054/labs/lab21/Examples/exrumen.htm\" xsd:string\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:121112:intersection_of: composed_primarily_of UBERON:0002418 ! cartilage tissue\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:121134:def: \"The epidermis is the entire outer epithelial layer of an animal, it may be a single layer that produces an extracellular material (e.g. the cuticle of arthropods) or a complex stratified squamous epithelium, as in the case of many vertebrate species[GO].\" [GO:0008544]\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:121451:intersection_of: composed_primarily_of GO:0031012 ! extracellular matrix\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:121469:intersection_of: composed_primarily_of GO:0045095 ! keratin filament\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:121480:intersection_of: composed_primarily_of CHEBI:17029 ! chitin\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:121546:relationship: composed_primarily_of UBERON:0001135 ! smooth muscle tissue\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:121556:relationship: composed_primarily_of UBERON:0002036 ! striated muscle tissue\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:121800:relationship: composed_primarily_of UBERON:0002384 {source=\"BTO\"} ! connective tissue\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:123942:intersection_of: composed_primarily_of UBERON:0002418 ! cartilage tissue\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:123978:intersection_of: composed_primarily_of UBERON:0011860 ! collection of collagen fibrils\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:124212:intersection_of: composed_primarily_of UBERON:0002481 ! bone tissue\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:124226:intersection_of: composed_primarily_of UBERON:0002481 ! bone tissue\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:124531:intersection_of: composed_primarily_of UBERON:0002418 ! cartilage tissue\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:127434:property_value: taxon_notes \"the forestomach accounts for about 60% (rat) and 70% (mouse) of the stomach volume and receives the esophagus at the cardiac antrum; the wall of the forestomach consists of, from inside to outside, stratified squamous epithelium, the lamina propria (epithelium and lamina propria form the mucosa), the muscularis mucosae, the submucosa, the muscularis interna and externa (inner circular and outer longitudinal layers of smooth muscle), and the serosa\" xsd:string\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:127706:relationship: composed_primarily_of UBERON:0007846 {source=\"VSAO\"} ! dense regular connective tissue\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:127812:relationship: composed_primarily_of UBERON:0001135 ! smooth muscle tissue\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:127930:relationship: composed_primarily_of UBERON:0001135 ! smooth muscle tissue\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:129036:intersection_of: composed_primarily_of UBERON:0002481 ! bone tissue\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:130497:relationship: composed_primarily_of UBERON:0003104 ! mesenchyme\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:130547:intersection_of: composed_primarily_of UBERON:0005866 ! pre-cartilage condensation\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:130570:intersection_of: composed_primarily_of UBERON:0002418 ! cartilage tissue\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:130616:intersection_of: composed_primarily_of UBERON:0005866 ! pre-cartilage condensation\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:130644:def: \"The limb epidermis is the outer epithelial layer of the limb, it is a complex stratified squamous epithelium.\" [GOC:dph, GOC:sdb_2009, GOC:tb]\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:130819:intersection_of: composed_primarily_of UBERON:0002418 ! cartilage tissue\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo: